content:
Instead of manually running and emailing a report to your team, you can subscribe to a report. Subscribe yourself and other users, groups, or roles to receive refreshed report results by email on a schedule that you set.

Available in: Lightning Experience
Available in: Essentials, Group, Platform, Professional, Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions

To subscribe to reports:
- Subscribe to Reports
- Subscribe to Reports: Add Recipients (to subscribe other people)
- Subscribe to Reports: Send to Groups and Roles (to subscribe by groups or roles)
- Subscribe to Reports: Set Running User (to specify who runs the report)

Watch a video:  Subscribe to Reports and Dashboards (Lightning Experience)

From the Reports tab, select | Subscribe. 
Set the subscription schedule.
To have the report results delivered as an attached file, click Attach File.
Select Formatted Report (.xlsx format) or Report Details (.csx format).

Add recipients or remove yourself. 
Under Run Report As, specify whose perspective is used when running the report.
Optionally, add conditions. The conditions are evaluated when the report is run according to the schedule you set.

The report subscription starts, and recipients begin receiving report results by email according to the schedule and conditions you set.
title: Subscribe to Reports in Salesforce Lightning Experience
